    <td colspan="3">Dear Local Official:</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="3">
Welcome, and thank you for joining me for the 2014 "Follow the Money" workshop series!</td></tr>
<tr><td width="60%">
As elected officials in Illinois, we all have a tremendous responsibility to make sure tax dollars are spent wisely and to protect the public trust. I'm eager to work with you in the coming months to help local governments become more transparent and efficient and to prevent fraud and corruption in all levels of government.<br /><Br /> 

With presentations and speakers from the Illinois CPA Society and the FBI, these workshops are sure to be chock full of great information we can use to improve our government and make it more accountable. We have a unique opportunity to work together, and that's what this series is all about!
<br />
</td>
    <td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
    <td><img src="/iwgraph/ComptrollerImg/Topinka.png" width="180" height="212" /></td>
  </tr>
 <tr><td colspan="3">I hope that you will take advantage of one of the many "Follow the Money" workshops across the state, and if you have any questions regarding the series, please call the Public Affairs Division at (855) 452-7587.<Br /><Br />
</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="3">
I look forward to working with you in the coming year. All the best in 2014!
</td></tr>
